Description of made changes:
- Fixed all compilation errors after updating guava version;
- Removed usage of some deprecated API;
- Shaded guava version and added dependencies to the shaded jar;
- To avoid bug with highlighting in IDE, unpacked shaded guava sources to the target source directory;
- Increased size for JDBC driver to 38000000 and 36000000 since both unshaded and shaded versions of guava should be included
- Replaced all guava imports with shaded ones and banned imports to the unshaded classes
- Replaced some guava methods for collections creating by constructors according to the recommendations in it's javadocs
- Replaced usage of some guava interfaces (Function, Predicate etc.) and methods (Sets.filter(), Iterables.tryFind, transform etc.) by java ones
- Added methods to convert shaded ImmutableList to unshaded one for the cases when another library has in its API ImmutableList.
